comment: Plumlee (POR) sets the screen on Henderson (PHI) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Aminu (POR) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Ilyasova (PHI) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court of a blocking foul was overturned.
Ilyasova (PHI) establishes legal guarding position outside of the RA during Lillard's (POR) drive to the basket and shot attempt.
McCollum (POR) makes contact with the ball on the drive to the basket by Saric (PHI).
Lillard (POR) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with McConnell (PHI) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
McConnell (PHI) makes contact with Plumlee (POR) that affects his SQBR.
Saric's (PHI) left foot is out of bounds when he makes contact with the loose ball.
[Detectable with stop watch] Plumlee (POR) is in the paint without actively guarding an opponent for longer than three seconds.
Henderson (PHI) makes body to body contact with Lillard (POR) that affects his SQBR.
[Observable in enhanced video] Saric (PHI) enters the paint area prior to the free throw being released.
Turner (POR) legally contests Covington's (PHI) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Noel (PHI) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Plumlee (POR) that does not affect his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
Plumlee (POR) makes marginal contact with Noel (PHI) on the play at the basket.
